race.comment: The penny has dropped for BRUCKHEIMER (2) who has strung back-to-back wins together and is racing with a lot of confidence of late. Winning rider Youngberry sticks and again gets the benefit of her 3kg claim. Rates the testing material. NO NAME FRANK (1) has gotten better with each run this time in and looks to be working up to another victory. Include in calculations. I'M ZAC (3) has placed over this course and distance and will find this easier than the recent Saturday metro outing. In the mix. JEROME (8) is stepping up in class after a last-start win by 0.8 lengths over 1200m at Warwick at huge odds. Has a liking for this trip and is worth consideration.
